# Final check for connectivity:
# Every entity created has at least one rdf:type and rdfs:label.
# Most entities are linked to others using NORIA properties.
# Agents are linked to resources, applications, trouble tickets, change requests.
# Resources are linked to product models, locations, network interfaces, applications, agents.
# Network interfaces are linked to resources and network links.
# Network links are linked to network interfaces and resources.
# Locations are linked to sites, rooms, and loci.
# Applications are linked to resources, application modules, services.
# Application modules are linked to applications, agents, services.
# Services are linked to applications/modules.
# Event records are linked to resources, applications, agents, trouble tickets, change requests.
# Trouble tickets are linked to services, resources, agents, event records, notes, change requests (implicitly via related events).
# Trouble ticket notes are linked to trouble tickets and agents.
# Change requests are linked to resources, applications, agents, event records.
# Operation plans are linked to pre/post conditions and event records (via alarmProposedRepairAction).
# Anomaly patterns are linked to trouble tickets (via dcterms:conformsTo).
# Document attachments are linked to trouble tickets and change requests.

# The graph is dense and interconnected, covering various aspects of IT infrastructure and operations.
